query.result:
19 The rain makes them howl like dogs;
20 they shelter one side with the other;
21 the wretched profane often turn around.

22 When Cerberus, the great worm, saw us,
23 he opened his mouths and showed us his tusks;
24 he had no limb that he held still.

58 I replied to him: "Ciacco, your suffering
59 weighs on me so much that it moves me to tears;
60 but tell me, if you know, what will become of

61 the citizens of the divided city;
62 if there is any just one among them; and tell me the reason
63 why such great discord has assailed it."

73 There are two just men, but they are not listened to;
74 pride, envy, and avarice are
75 the three sparks that have set their hearts on fire."

82 tell me where they are and let me know them;
83 for a great desire compels me to know
84 if Heaven sweetens them or Hell embitters them."

85 And he: "They are among the blackest souls;
86 different sins weigh them down to the bottom:
87 if you descend so far, you will be able to see them there.

91 Then he twisted his straight eyes into squinting ones;
92 he looked at me a little and then bowed his head:
93 with it he fell beside the other blind ones.

